      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "This project can report observed patterns in the anonymized data and produce a directional, decision-support ranking of pages for human review. It can compare whether highly ranked pages contain more measured decline or opportunity signals than a simple baseline. It cannot prove that refreshing a page causes traffic recovery, guarantee that a recommended action will improve performance, or claim to predict Google’s algorithm. In the starter dataset, the declining label is defined from trend_direction, which is calculated from trend_pct; therefore it represents a measured historical rule rather than an independently observed future outcome. A future-prediction claim would require separate past feature and future outcome windows from the warehouse data."
